cs.WEB, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.DB

The paper discusses the W3C Open Annotation Data Model, which is primarily used for annotating web content. This falls under the category of Web Science (cs.WEB). The paper also mentions semantic annotations, which are related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the use of deep learning (cs.DL) and databases (cs.DB) may be relevant in implementing and managing these annotations.
